                                                                                            <customfield id="customfield_12310192" key="com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.customfieldtypes:textarea">
                        <customfieldname>Release Note</customfieldname>
                        <customfieldvalues>
                            <customfieldvalue>This change enables various hadoop properties to be passed to the LauncherTask via webhcat-site.xml.&lt;br/&gt;
Earlier hadoop properties in webhcat-site.xml would get used in most other places, except for the launch of the LauncherTask. Only a few parameters could be set, and they had to be set using templeton.* parameters. For example templeton.mapper.memory.mb was used to set mapreduce.map.memory.mb.</customfieldvalue>

                        </customfieldvalues>
